        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Mobile Food Court Van&amp;quot; scheme is implemented by the Dr. Ambedkar Antyodaya Development Corporation (DAADC) under the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Government of Gujarat. The scheme aims to generate self-employment opportunities in the food and beverage sector by providing loan assistance to unemployed scheduled caste individuals belonging to Antyodaya families. Under this scheme, loan is provided to the eligible beneficiaries at a concessional interest rate.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Loan Amount:** Up to ₹6,00,000/-\n**Interest Rate:** 6% per annum\n**Contribution:**\n\n- State Government Contribution: 95 %\n- Beneficiary Contribution: 5%\n\n**Possible Installment Amount:**\n\n- ₹11,020/- per month (for 5 years)\n- ₹ 9,447/- per month (for 6 years)\n- ₹ 8,327/- per month (for 7 years)\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to generate self-employment opportunities in the food and beverage sector by providing credit to unemployed scheduled caste individuals belonging to Antyodaya families. Under this scheme, loans are provided to the eligible beneficiaries at a concessional interest rate.",
